![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1587582289290-A50UIL7V85XF012HAIHY/123.jpg?format=original)

The world has become a very unpredictable place. With misinformation at every turn, citizens are starting to lose hope in the things they always stood for, wondering if the old way of life has become too "old fashioned". Seems like that was also the case in early 2001 in the offices of DC Comics as they wondered if their first hero Superman, needed to change with the times. That brings us **Action Comics #775** where a question is asked; **_What's So Funny Bout Truth Justice & The American Way_**? In the issue, Superman meets The Elite, a no-nonsense teel of vigilantes that challenge his code of Ethics. Will the man of Steel be swayed? Tune into this review and find out!  
  
If you can, please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by [**ComicBookClique.com**](/comicbookclique/episode/update/id/Comicbokclique.com), the home for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  
  
